PEOPLE living with disabilities have answered President Cyril Ramaphosa’s challenge and joined the Jerusalema dance challenge.  ALSO READ: DJ ZINHLE TAKES OVER AS CEO OF BOULEVARD ROSE' Those who viewed the clip applauded the participants for not allowing their disabilities to stand in their way. Bonnie Boniswa KaMaqhawe wrote: “Have fun and be safe.” Last month during his national address, Ramaphosa congratulated Master KG and Nomcebo Zikode for making the song, which has become a global, sensation and encouraged South Africans to participate in the dance challenge. During his speech, he said: “There can be no better way to celebrate our South Africans than joining the global phenomenon that is spreading across the world and that is the Jerusalema dance challenge.” 